01:34:36,876 --> 01:34:46,464
i just thought we've lost one of the most creative minds of our generation.

01:34:46,700 --> 01:34:49,728
I was like the whole world fell apart at that moment.

01:34:56,960 --> 01:34:59,114
It was one of the hardest nights of my life.

01:35:00,117 --> 01:35:03,914
It was like I was screaming "I can't hear you.. what did you just say.. I can't hear you."

01:35:07,468 --> 01:35:11,765
I can't. Thats it.

01:35:19,978 --> 01:35:23,712
None of it made any sense. And really still doesn't.

01:35:24,693 --> 01:35:27,488
I was so frustrated and angry.

01:35:38,154 --> 01:35:41,120
You know I tried to explain it to my kids.

01:35:41,370 --> 01:35:46,325
My 3 yr old told me that the doctors would fix him.

01:35:52,021 --> 01:35:56,160
I know lots of people who have died but I've never lost anybody like this.

01:35:56,245 --> 01:36:03,050
Because everybody feels, and I do too, there is so much that we could've.. more to do.

01:36:04,672 --> 01:36:10,059
I just didn't know that he was there. I didn't know this is what he was suffering.

01:36:11,242 --> 01:36:13,601
He was part of me.

01:36:15,253 --> 01:36:19,328
And I just wanted it to not be real.

01:36:23,466 --> 01:36:27,989
And then I just looked at his Wikipedia page and I saw the end date.

01:36:32,065 --> 01:36:34,944
02-02-2013

